## 5. Security Architecture

### JWT Token Strategy

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                       JWT Payload                        │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  sub        : "1"                (user ID)               │
│  email      : "admin@acme.com"                           │
│  role       : "ADMIN"                                    │
│  tenantId   : "acme-tenant-uuid"                         │
│  iat        : 1700000000         (issued at)             │
│  exp        : 1700003600         (expires in 1 hour)     │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- **Access Token**: Short-lived (1 hour). Sent in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.
- **Refresh Token**: Long-lived (7 days). Stored in `HttpOnly` secure cookie. Used to issue new access tokens silently.
- **Secret**: RSA 256 asymmetric key (or HS256 HMAC with a strong env-variable secret).

### Request Security Layers

```
Incoming Request
      │
      ▼
[1] CORS Filter         — Whitelist allowed origins
      │
      ▼
[2] Rate Limiter        — Prevent brute-force (Bucket4j)
      │
      ▼
[3] JWT Auth Filter     — Validate token, extract claims
      │
      ▼
[4] Tenant Context      — Set tenant_id in ThreadLocal
      │
      ▼
[5] Spring Security     — Role-based authorization
      │
      ▼
[6] Controller          — Business logic
      │
      ▼
[7] Hibernate Filter    — WHERE tenant_id = :tenantId (auto-appended)
      │
      ▼
[8] Tenant Context Cleanup — ThreadLocal.remove()
```

